arm_group.description: Standard of care therapy as per local practice

brief_summary.textblock:
This study will contribute to the evaluation of long-term safety, tolerability and efficacy
      of evolocumab (AMG 145) in subjects with hyperlipidemia and subjects with mixed
      dyslipidemia.

clinical_study.brief_title: Open Label Study of Long Term Evaluation Against LDL-C Trial-2

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

        - Complete a qualifying evolocumab (AMG 145) parent study

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Experienced a treatment-related serious adverse event that led to IP discontinuation
             in the parent study

          -  Have an unstable medical condition, in the judgment of the investigator

          -  Known sensitivity to any of the products to be administered during dosing

          -  Currently enrolled in another investigational device or drug study (excluding
             evolocumab (AMG 145) parent study), or less than 30 days since ending another
             investigational device or drug study(s),or receiving other investigational agent(s)

intervention.description: evolocumab (AMG 145) is a fully human monoclonal antibody against PCSK9. Standard of care therapy is per local practice; this could include prescribed therapies and/or dietary/exercise regimes
Standard of care therapy as per local practices. This could include prescribed therapies and/or dietary/exercise regimes

clinical_study.official_title: A Multicenter, Controlled, Open-label Extension (OLE) Study to Assess the Long-term Safety and Efficacy of AMG 145-2
